7;\n    var classes = [];\n    var colorramp = [];\n   \n    if (vals.length > 1) {\n\t//var series = new geostats(vals.sort(function (a, b) {  return a - b;  }));\n\tvar series = new geostats(vals);\n\tif (series.getClassUniqueValues().length <= 7) { numranges = series.getClassUniqueValues().length - 1; } //if less than 7 unique values in the dataset, set range down to uniques...\n\tclasses = series.getClassJenks(numranges);\n\tfor(i=0;i<classes.length;i++) { classes[i] = classes[i] * 1; } //fix bug in geostats that returns middle classes as numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\tif (classes[0] == 0 && classes[1] == 0) { classes.shift(); numranges--; } //if first two elements are 0, then drop the second... happens sometimes oddly...\n\t\n\t//if we have less than 7 ranges, see if we can boost the number of ranges by splitting off some of the upper values...\n\tif (numranges < 7) {\n\t    for(i=classes.length-2;i>=0;i--) {\n\t    \tif (numranges < 7) {\n\t    \t    classes.splice(i+1, 0, ((classes[i] + classes[i+1])/2));\n\t\t    i--;\n\t\t    numranges++;\n\t\t}\n\t    }\n\t}\n\t\n    } else if (vals.length == 1) {\n    \t//just one data point, so just treat as single class...\n\tnumranges = -1; //stop the colorramp code from running, since we\'re going to manually set here...\n\tclasses[0] = vals[0];\n\tclasses[1] = vals[0];\n\tcolorramp[0] = \'#800026\';\n    } else {\n    \t//no data of any kind...\n    }\n    \n    /* ########################################### */\n    //calculate our dynamic color ramp based on the number of classes...\n    var color_start = 0xFFEDA0, color_end = 0x800026;\n    rs = (color_start & 0xff0000) >> 16; \n    gs = (color_start & 0x00ff00) >> 8; \n    bs = (color_start & 0x0000ff) >> 0; \n    re = (color_end & 0xff0000) >> 16; \n    ge = (color_end & 0x00ff00) >> 8; \n    be = (color_end & 0x0000ff) >> 0;\n    \n    function interpolate(start, end, step, numsteps) { \n\tif (start < end) {\n\t    return ((end - start) * (step / numsteps)) + start; \n\t} else {\n\t    return ((start - end) * (1 - (step / numsteps))) + end;\n\t}\n    }\n    \n    for(i=0;i<numranges;i++) {\n    \tr = interpolate(rs, re, i, numranges-1); \n    \tg = interpolate(gs, ge, i, numranges-1); \n    \tb = interpolate(bs, be, i, numranges-1);   \n\tcolor = ((( r << 8 ) |  g ) << 8 ) | b;\n\tcolorramp[i] = \'#\' + color.toString(16);\n    }\n    /* ########################################### */\n\n\n\n\t//var map = L.map(\'map\', \'Insufficient Data\' : props.density + \'%\') : \'Hover over a location\');\n\t};\n\n\tinfo.addTo(map);\n\n\tfunction getColor(v) {\n\t    if (v == undefined) { return \'#CCCCCC\'; }\n\t    for(i=classes.length-2;i >= 0;i--) { //skip the last class, since that is just the endcap...\n\t\tif (v >= classes[i]) { return colorramp[i]; }\n\t    }\n\t\n\t}\n\t\n\n\tfunction style(feature) {\n\t\treturn {\n\t\t\tweight: 0.3,\n\t\t\topacity: 0.5,\n\t\t\tcolor: \'\',\n\t\t\tdashArray: \'3\',\n\t\t\tfillOpacity: 0.7,\n\t\t\tfillColor: getColor(feature.properties.density)\n\t\t};\n\t}\n\n\tfunction highlightFeature(e) {\n\t\tvar layer = e.target;\n\n\t\tlayer.setStyle({\n\t\t\tweight: 5,\n\t\t\tcolor: \'#666\',\n\t\t\tdashArray: \'\',\n\t\t\tfillOpacity: 0.8\n\t\t});\n\n\t\tif (!L.Browser.ie && !L.Browser.opera && !L.Browser.edge) {\n\t\t\tlayer.bringToFront();\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tinfo.update(layer.feature.properties);\n\t}\n\n\tvar geojson;\n\n\tfunction resetHighlight(e) {\n\t\tgeojson.resetStyle(e.target);\n\t\tinfo.update();\n\t}\n\n\tfunction makepopup(e) {\n\t\t//map.fitBounds(e.target.getBounds());\n\t\thtml = \'<div STYLE="height: 130px; width: 231px; background: #000000; background-position: center; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-image: url(\\\'/assets/images/loader.gif\\\');"><img src="\' + data_shareimage[e.gnsadm1] + \'" STYLE="height: 130px; width: 231px; display: inline; object-fit: cover;" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src=\\\'data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAUEBAAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\\\';"></div>\';\n\t\thtml = html + \'<H1 STYLE="color: white;bottom: 220px;position: absolute; line-height: 1em;padding-left: 10px;text-shadow: 1px 1px #000000; font-size: 1.8em">\' + e.name + \'</H1>\';\n\t\thtml = html + \'<DIV STYLE="padding: 10px 0px 10px 0px; display: inline-block; width: 231px; height: 200px; background: #ffffff; " ss-container>\' + (data_html[e.gnsadm1] == undefined ? \'No Data\' : data_html[e.gnsadm1]) + \'<br><br></DIV>\';\n\t\thtml += \'<DIV STYLE="position: absolute; top: 327px; width: 200px; height: 12px; left: 10px; z-index: 10;" CLASS="bottomfeather"></DIV>\';\n\t\treturn html;\n\t}\n\n\tfunction onEachFeature(feature, layer) {\n\t\tlayer.on({ mouseover: highlightFeature, mouseout: resetHighlight });\n\t\tlayer.bindPopup(makepopup(feature.properties), { minWidth: 230, maxWidth: 230, maxHeight: 350, className: \'popupCustom\' }).on(\'click\', function() { SimpleScrollbar.initAll(); } );\n\t}\n\t\n\tgeojson = L.geoJson(adm1map, { style: style, onEachFeature: onEachFeature }).addTo(map);\n\n\n\tvar legend = L.control({position: \'bottomright\'});\n\n\tlegend.onAdd = function (map) {\n\n\t\tvar div = L.DomUtil.create(\'div\', \'info legend\');\n\t\tvar labels = [], from, to;\n\n\t\t//add the "no data" label...\n\t\tlabels.push(\'<i style="background:#CCCCCC"></i> No Data\');\n\t\t\n\t\t//now do the real labels..\n\t\tfor (var i = 0; i < classes.length - 1; i++) {\n\t\t\tfrom = classes[i];\n\t\t\tto = classes[i + 1];\n\t\t\tlabels.push(\'<i style="background:\' + getColor(from) + \'"></i> \' + from + (to ? \'&ndash;\' + to : \'+\'));\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdiv.innerHTML = labels.join(\'<br>\');\n\t\treturn div;\n\t};\n\n\tlegend.addTo(map);\n\n</script>\n\n<link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/simple-scrollbar/simple-scrollbar.css"></script>\n<!--[if IE 9]><script src="/assets/js/classList-2014-01-31/classList.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n<script src="/assets/js/simple-scrollbar/simple-scrollbar.min.js"></script>\n\t\n<script type="text/javascript">\n\n  var _gaq = _gaq || [];\n  _gaq.push([\'_setAccount\', \'UA-47450367-1\']);\n  _gaq.push([\'_setDomainName\', \'.gdeltproject.org\']);\n  _gaq.push([\'_trackPageview\']);\n\n  (function() {\n    var ga = document.createElement(\'script\'); ga.type = \'text/javascript\'; ga.async = true;\n    ga.src = (\'https:\' == document.location.protocol ?
